pple%2C%20Gmail%2C%20Telegram%2C%20Facebook%2C%20GitHub%2C%20and%20more%2C%20researchers%20at%20Cybernews%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcybernews.com%2Fsecurity%2Fbillions-credentials-exposed-infostealers-data-leak%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBad%20actors%20now%20have%20%26quot%3Bunprecedented%20access%20to%20personal%20credentials%20that%20can%20be%20used%20for%20account%20takeover%2C%20identity%20theft%2C%20and%20highly%20targeted%20phishing%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20exposed%20people%20or%20accounts%20is%20unknown.%20The%20researchers%20said%20the%20data%20likely%20comes%20from%20malicious%20software%20known%20as%20infostealers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat's%20especially%20concerning%20is%20the%20structure%20and%20recency%20of%20these%20datasets%20%E2%80%94%20these%20aren't%20just%20old%20breaches%20being%20recycled.%20This%20is%20fresh%2C%20weaponizable%20intelligence%20at%20scale%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECybernews%20said%20researchers%20uncovered%20the%20leak%20when%20the%20datasets%20were%20exposed%20for%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20follows%20the%20May%20discovery%20of%20a%20database%20containing%20more%20than%20184%20million%20credentials%2C%20including%20Apple%2C%20Facebook%2C%20and%20Google%20logins%2C%20Wired%20earlier%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fmysterious-database-logins-governments-social-media%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20nervous%20that%20your%20logins%20are%20at%20risk%2C%20there%20are%20steps%20you%20can%20take%20to%20make%20your%20account%20safer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229fb8050f-cb41-434e-900c-d8b89f66bc11%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20protect%20yourself%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can't%20unring%20the%20bell%20of%20an%20information%20leak.%20However%2C%20you%20can%20take%20steps%20to%20identify%20if%20your%20credentials%20have%20been%20involved%20in%20any%20data%20breaches%20and%20protect%20yourself%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20check%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhaveibeenpwned.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esites%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Have%20I%20Been%20Pwned%20to%20see%20if%20your%20email%20has%20appeared%20in%20a%20data%20breach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurning%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Ftwo-factor-authentication%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etwo-step%20authentication%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20your%20accounts%20can%20also%20help%20protect%20them%20from%20unauthorized%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlatforms%20also%20offer%20resources%20to%20help%20users%20secure%20their%20accounts.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20encourages%20users%20to%20use%20protections%20that%20don't%20require%20a%20password%2C%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeath-of-passwords-login-passkeys-google-apple-face-id-biometrics-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epasskey%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20tech%20giants%2C%20along%20with%20Apple%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Microsoft%2C%20that%20have%20been%20working%20to%20move%20users%20away%20from%20passwords%20to%20help%20secure%20their%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20prefer%20to%20stick%20with%20passwords%2C%20Google's%20password%20manager%20can%20store%20login%20credentials%20and%20notify%20users%20if%20they%20appear%20in%20a%20breach%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-google-dark-web-report-personal-data-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20dark%20web%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20free%20tool%20that%20tracks%20whether%20personal%20information%20is%20floating%20around%20in%20online%20databases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGitHub%2C%20an%20online%20coding%20platform%2C%20offers%20developers%20a%20guide%20on%20how%20to%20implement%20safety%20measures%20in%20their%20organizations.%20The%20site%20recommends%20creating%20a%20security%20policy%2C%20having%20strict%20password%20guidelines%2C%20and%20requiring%20two-factor%20authorization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20leak%20included%20logs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%26quot%3Boften%20with%20tokens%2C%20cookies%2C%20and%20metadata%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20makes%20it%20%26quot%3Bparticularly%20dangerous%20for%20organizations%20lacking%20multi-factor%20authentication%20or%20credential%20hygiene%20practices%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Cybernews%20team%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20offers%20a%20Privacy%20Checkup%20tool%20for%20users%20to%20review%20their%20privacy%20and%20security%20account%20settings.%20There%2C%20you%20can%20turn%20on%20two-factor%20authentication%20and%20ensure%20Meta%20alerts%20you%20of%20unusual%20logins.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Telegram%20said%20its%20primary%20login%20method%20sends%20a%20one-time%20password%20to%20users%20over%20SMS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%2C%20this%20is%20far%20less%20relevant%20for%20Telegram%20users%20compared%20to%20other%20platforms%20where%20the%20password%20is%20always%20the%20same%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Telegram%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20about%20the%20data%20leak.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%2C%20GitHub%2C%20and%20Meta%20did%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20on%20the%20data%20leak.%20Google%20said%20it%20was%20directing%20users%20to%20some%20of%20the%20security%20resources%20above.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-protect-accounts-data-breach-password-leaks-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750441593000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68558668f748d8c055f410e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-protect-accounts-data-